replies.body:
In regards of the inability to use SSN as a means of account verification;

There's also the cell phone number which Riot has used as a anti-smurf countermeasure in Clash. Although it can be circumvented by using friends and family phone numbers, it would certainly slow down account sellers from farming as many ranked accounts unless their profit margins were enough to buy more cell phone numbers. It would also cap off how many accounts a single person could smurf seeing as the amount of numbers you can collect and smurf depend on how many friends you can make and are willing to share the number with you.

But a problem lies with the case where a player decides to switch phone numbers for various reasons. There could be number mismatching or collisions if the number you switched too was already associated with an active account.
